# Maintainer: copy to distribution/npm/release-tag-message.local (gitignored).
# Keep VERSION exactly once in the Release line below.
#
# This file drives (1) the annotated git tag and (2) the top of the GitHub Release
# page after CI runs (see scripts/create-github-release-from-tag.sh). Longer prose
# is fine here; do not commit per-version notes to the repo. CI appends generated
# PR bullets after a --- separator when a previous v*.*.* tag exists.

Release @aguil/agents VERSION: One-line summary of this tag (replace this sentence).

Optional paragraphs for audience-facing notes go here. This .example file is committed as a format contract only; your real annotation text lives in release-tag-message.local (gitignored) or another path you pass with --message-file.
